  <original-body>I'm using RailsAdmin and I've found something strange.

If I use an initializer that is doing some setup for RailsAdmin, the default_locale of the Rails app is set to `:en` because of a call to `translate` before the Rails app has a chance to apply it's own setup from `config/application.rb`

Here is a ticket for RailsAdmin that describes how I've found this to be an issue :
https://github.com/sferik/rails_admin/issues/issue/187/#issue/187</original-body>
